    public class Tank
extends LevelObject
implements Explosion
    Represents the Tanks of a level generated from level file based on their initial position.

    • Constructor Detail

      • Tank

        public Tank(Level level,
            java.lang.Integer x,
            java.lang.Integer y,
            Player player)
        Creates a tank by associating the Level it belongs to, the starting x and y position, and the player this tanks belong to. The health is set at 100, fuel at 250 and power 50 when a new tank is created.
        Parameters:
        level - Level Object that the tank belongs to.
        x - Initial x-position
        y - Initial y-position
        player - Player object that the tank belongs to.

        public void draw(App app)
        Draws the tank object on the screen at the defined position. Tank is made up of a rectangle, semicircle and a line. Tank activity is checked first before drawing. Tank parachute is drawn when in use.
